Further, in this disorder issues are of special use, particularly an issue between the first and second cervical vertebrae, for in that position, close to the origin ol the disease, it has the greater efficacy. And the usefulness of issues consists in this, that they largely contribute to the evacuation of the super- fluous serosity oi the hrain, and so to the diminution of its abnormal siae, and also to the drying up oi the excessive humidity of the spinal marrow, and conse- quently to the strengthening ol the nerves thence arising. A seton can supply the place of an issue.
